Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportCapViolation(25.10)                            reportCapViolation(25.10)

Name
       reportCapViolation  -  After  timing analysis, reports nets that exceed
       the maximum capacitance constraints in the timing  library  and  timing
       constraints file

Syntax
       reportCapViolation

       [-help]

       [-all | -noGlobalNets]

       [-max]

       [-min]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-selNetFile <fileName>]

       [-excNetFile <fileName>]

       [-significant_digits <integer>]

       [-useDrcMargin]

       After timing analysis, reports nets that exceed the maximum capacitance
       constraints in the timing library and timing constraints file. Run this
       command  after running timing analysis (timeDesign) or timing optimiza-
       tion (optDesign).

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for each reportCapViolation parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:  man reportCapViolation

       -all   Reports  capacitance violations for all nets in the design. This
              is the default option.

       -excNetFile <f><ileName>
              Specifies the file that contains the hierarchical net names that
              are excluded from the capacitance violation report.

       -noGlobalNets
              Reports capacitance violations on all nets except for power  and
              ground nets.

              Note: The parameters, -all and -noGlobalNets are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -max   Reports only maximum capacitance violations. This is the default
              option.

       -min   Reports only minimum capacitance violations.

              Note: The parameters, -min and -max are mutually exclusive.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the file to which the results are written.

       -selNetFile <f><ileName>
              Specifies  the file that contains the hierarchical net names for
              the report. Only these net names are considered for inclusion in
              the capacitance violation report.

              Note: The parameters, -selNetFile and -excNetFile are not  mutu-
              ally  exclusive.  If both parameters are specified, the -excNet-
              File parameter overides the -selNetFile parameter.

       -significant_digits <integer>
              Allows the user to specify the number of significant digits.

              Default: 3

       -useDrcMargin
              Generates the report using the margin value that you specify us-
              ing the -drcMargin parameter of the setOptModecommand.

Example
       The following command reports nets that exceed the maximum  capacitance
       constraints in the report file maxcap.report:

       reportCapViolation -outfile maxCap.report

